# Sora Video Generation via Browser Automation

Generate AI videos using TabzChrome MCP tools.

## Quick Start

```
Generate a {{duration:10s|10s|15s}} video of {{subject:a cozy coding scene}}
```

## Fillable Fields

| Field | Options | Notes |
|-------|---------|-------|
| `{{duration}}` | 10s, 15s | 15s uses more credits |
| `{{aspect}}` | 16:9, 9:16, 1:1 | Landscape, portrait, square |
| `{{style}}` | cinematic, anime, realistic, artistic | Add to prompt |
| `{{subject}}` | (free text) | Main subject of video |

## Workflow

### 1. Open Sora Drafts Page (has prompt input + shows your videos)
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_open_url '{"url": "https://sora.chatgpt.com/drafts"}'
```

### 2. Wait for page load, then fill prompt
```bash
# Wait 2-3 seconds for page to load
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_fill '{"selector": "textarea", "value": "{{prompt}}"}'
```

### 3. Submit (Click Create video)
```bash
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_click '{"selector": "div.absolute.bottom-2 button.inline-flex:last-child"}'
```

### 4. Wait for generation (60-120 seconds)
Videos appear in "Drafts" section when complete.

```bash
# Check for completion notification or thumbnail change
mcp-cli call tabz/tabz_screenshot '{}'
```

### 5. Save generated video
Download videos to:
```
.prompts/AI_Videos/
```
Create folder if it doesn't exist. Contents are gitignored (your videos stay local).

## Key Selectors

| Element | Selector |
|---------|----------|
| Prompt textarea | `textarea` |
| Create video button | `div.absolute.bottom-2 button.inline-flex:last-child` |
| Settings button | `button#radix-:rj:` (near textarea) |
| Profile link | `div.flex.flex-col.items-center a:last-of-type` |
| Drafts card (on profile) | `a.relative.block.h-full.w-full.overflow-hidden` |
| Video thumbnail | `video` |

## URLs

| Page | URL | Notes |
|------|-----|-------|
| Drafts | `sora.chatgpt.com/drafts` | **Start here** - has prompt + your videos |
| Profile | `sora.chatgpt.com/profile` | Shows drafts card (blurred preview) |
| Explore | `sora.chatgpt.com/explore` | Community videos feed |

## First-Time Setup

On first video creation, Sora shows a **Media Upload Agreement** modal:
1. Check all 4 checkboxes: `[role=checkbox]`
2. Click Accept button

After accepting once, it won't show again.

## Duration Options

Sora supports:
- **10 seconds** - Standard (default)
- **15 seconds** - Longer scenes (uses more credits)

Access via Settings button near the prompt input.

## Example Prompts

### Developer/Tech Scene (TabzChrome vibe)
```
A developer working late at night, their screen glowing in a dark room.
They open a Chrome browser sidebar revealing multiple terminal windows.
The camera zooms into the screen showing colorful terminal output scrolling,
then they type a command and AI-generated text appears.
Cozy lo-fi aesthetic, soft desk lamp light, rain on window.
```

### Product Demo
```
Smooth screen recording style video showing a browser extension sidebar
opening from the right side of Chrome. Multiple terminal tabs appear
with colorful text. A cursor clicks between tabs. Modern, clean UI,
soft shadows, professional product demo aesthetic.
```

### Abstract/Artistic
```
Digital streams of code flowing through a neon-lit cyberpunk cityscape.
Binary rain falls past glowing terminal windows floating in space.
Camera slowly pushes through layers of holographic UI elements.
Blade Runner meets Matrix aesthetic, moody blue and orange lighting.
```

## Tips

1. **Start from Drafts** - Has prompt input + shows all your generated videos
2. **Be cinematic** - Describe camera movements: "camera zooms", "slowly pans", "tracking shot"
3. **Mention lighting** - "soft lamp light", "neon glow", "golden hour"
4. **Add atmosphere** - "rain on window", "dust particles in light", "lens flare"
5. **Reference styles** - "lo-fi aesthetic", "cinematic", "product demo style"
6. **Multiple videos** - Queue several prompts, they generate in parallel
